 ## Template Base
 
-This project follows the structure and conventions of `D:\SIPECOM\repository-git\cer-gcp\template-microservice`. When adding new features, cross-reference that template for:
-
-- **Package layout**: `infrastructure/adapter/in/web/{controller,dto}`, `infrastructure/security/`, `infrastructure/config/`
-- **REST API pattern**: versioned endpoints at `/api/v1/`, GET + POST dual endpoints, `@RequestParam` for GET, `@RequestBody` for POST, OpenAPI annotations (`@Tag`, `@Operation`, `@ApiResponse`, `@Schema`)
-- **Security**: `SecurityConfig` (stateless JWT, CSRF disabled), `JwtTokenProvider` (jjwt 0.12.x), `JwtAuthenticationFilter` — public paths: `/api/v1/auth/**`, `/actuator/**`, `/api-docs/**`, `/swagger-ui/**`
-- **Logging**: `LoggingEnrichmentFilter` injects `correlation_id` into MDC from `X-Correlation-ID` header for GCP structured log traceability
-- **OpenAPI**: `springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui:2.8.5`; UI at `/swagger-ui.html`, docs at `/api-docs`
-- **Build/deploy**: `build.sh` (Podman), `skaffold.yaml` (v4beta11), `docker/dev/Dockerfile` (dev profile), `k8s/namespace.yaml` (`ns-cer-suite-dev`)
-- **Profiles**: `local` (machine dev + local SQL), `dev` (GCP dev env vars), `prod` (GCP prod env vars)
-- **GcpConfig**: placeholder `@Configuration` for explicit GCP beans beyond auto-config
-
-Template deviations specific to this project:
-- Services live in `service/` (not `application/service/`) — large parser/generator do not fit the application-layer pattern
-- No `ScheduledTaskAdapter` — this service has no scheduled jobs
-- No `EncryptionUtils` — uses Cloud KMS via `KmsDecryptionAdapter` / `NoOpKmsDecryptionAdapter`
-- Primary inbound adapter is `PubSubSalesAdapter` (async), not an HTTP controller
+Reference project: `D:\SIPECOM\repository-git\cer-gcp\template-microservice`.
+
+This template defines the **structural conventions** to follow in this and all SuiteCloud microservices. It is a reference — apply only the patterns that make sense for each service's actual responsibilities.
+
+### Conventions that apply to this project
+
+- **Package layout** (hexagonal): `domain/{model,port/{in,out}}`, `service/`, `infrastructure/adapter/{in,out}`, `infrastructure/config/`
+- **Build/deploy artifacts**: `build.sh` (Podman + Skaffold `$IMAGE` support), `skaffold.yaml` (v4beta11), `docker/dev/Dockerfile` (dev image with `SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=dev`), `k8s/namespace.yaml` (`ns-cer-suite-dev`)
+- **Profiles**: `local` (developer machine, local SQL + GCP credentials file), `dev` (GCP dev, env vars), `prod` (GCP prod, env vars)
+- **Exception handling**: `@RestControllerAdvice` with RFC 7807 `ProblemDetail` — already implemented as `SuiteCloudExceptionHandler`
+- **Domain models**: immutable Java `record`s; mutations return copies via `with*()` methods
+- **Virtual threads**: `spring.threads.virtual.enabled: true`; no `synchronized` — use `ReentrantLock`/`Semaphore`
+
+### Template patterns NOT used in this project (and why)
+
+| Pattern | Reason not applied |
+|---------|-------------------|
+| REST controllers + DTOs (`/api/v1/**`) | This service is async (Pub/Sub only); no HTTP business endpoints |
+| `SecurityConfig` + JWT (`JwtTokenProvider`, `JwtAuthenticationFilter`) | No HTTP endpoints to protect; `spring-boot-starter-security` and `jjwt` deps are reserved for future use |
+| `LoggingEnrichmentFilter` (MDC `correlation_id`) | No inbound HTTP requests; correlation is tracked via Pub/Sub message attributes |
+| `GcpConfig` placeholder | GCP beans auto-configure via `jlib-pubsub-logging`, `jlib-firestore`, `jlib-kms` |
+| OpenAPI / Swagger (`springdoc-openapi`) | No REST API to document |
+| `ScheduledTaskAdapter` | No scheduled jobs in this service |
+| `EncryptionUtils` (Base64) | Encryption via Cloud KMS (`KmsDecryptionAdapter` / `NoOpKmsDecryptionAdapter`) |
+| `application/service/` package | Services are large domain-specific engines (parser, generator); `service/` is sufficient |
 
